               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> OSENEY (North). An amended agreement between <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename>, the abbot</persName>, 
               and <orgName key="org_107015">convent of Thame</orgName>, and the <orgName key="org_109067">abbot and convent of Oseney</orgName>, by which 
               they covenant to pay 36s. and 8d. to Oseney in recompense for the small tithes of North Oseney, 
               upon which <orgName key="org_107009">[Rewley] abbey</orgName>, of the foundation of 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Edmund</forename>, Earl of <placeName role="earl" type="earldom">Cornwall</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
               had been nearby built, until 1/2 a mark of annual rent shall be restored to Oseney from a piece of land 
               near the chapel of <placeName role="chapel" key="place_109209">Frees</placeName>, which
               <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> de <surname>Crocford</surname>
                        </persName> held of the said canons, and 
               30s. of rent be provided from some other source. 
               Dated at <placeName key="place_109514">Thame</placeName> on the day of the Assumption B.V.M., <origDate when="1281">1281</origDate>. 
                
                </p>
                  </msItem>
